text: Very upsetting experience today. I drove 30 minutes to come here and was informed they were out of the ingredients to make quite a few sandwiches. I then asked where the next Quiznos was and they listed off a bunch that have recently closed. So I asked where subway is and they stated they didn't know because they aren't from the area. You work here. You know. Terrible experience.

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BYOB': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'Corkage': 'False', 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False'}
categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Salad, Fast Food, Soup, Delis
text: Would never come back to this Quiznos again. We showed up at 10:50am on Sunday and sign says doesn't open till 11am, which i can respect so I waited in my car till 11am and then I go to the door and the lights are still out and it appears that an employee had just arrived and she is giving my wife and I the one minute signal through the window. We stand outside and wait, mind you it's winter and cold. We wait a couple minutes outside and then a second employee arrived and says to us "it's not open yet"? The  employee inside lets the other one in and proceeds to tell us to wait longer in which it is 11:05 at this time and none of the veggies and sandwich meat had been out so we decided to go somewhere else. They could have at least allowed us to wait inside. Clearly punctuality is not important to the employees of this store.

text:
I haven't eaten at a Quiznos in about 4 years when I moved from Cali to here.....   And the sandwich was just blah.  Not as good as I remember. I'll stick with Port of Subs.

Pros:  You can get your own pickles, peppers extras 
does have a yelp check in coupon ( $1 OFF a Regular or Large Sub or Large Salad)
Does have outside setting 

Cons:
parking is tight unless you park in Home Depot parking lot side.

text:
The girl who did my sandwich didn't ask me much before she started putting condiments and stuff on my bread. I asked for a turkey sandwich with avocado and she starts putting on mayo on it... 
She also took her gloves off and ran outside to look at a plane in the middle of making my sandwich. I was the only customer in there. 
The other woman who was in charge of my veggies seemed bothered by my presence. She didn't give me choices or anything. 
I give it 2 stars instead of one because alas, it did not kill me... but, I will not be returning anytime soon.

text:
This Quiznos is a very poorly managed Quiznos. I had a girlfriend that worked here and I found out that the management team not only makes the employees clock out when it's slow, but there the only Quiznos in town that still charge for the rosemary Parmesan bread and they also don't give you the correct portions of meat for your sandwich. The owner, Benny, is a cheep Asian man who is looking to screw the employees and the customers to save a buck! 
DO NOT TRUST THIS BUISNESS!

text: Kenneth was amazing. Never had someone at a chain sandwich shop put in the amount of effort that he did. Greeted me with a smile, was patient with my complex order, and over all very friendly. He deserves a raise and should be congratulated on being an awesome employee.

text: I have been a fan of Quiznos for many years. Although their prices tend to jump around and the menu often changes, I'm happy that they continue to serve my favorite, "The Traditional". I'm a lover of hot sandwiches and their toaster ovens are the best (can I get one for home?) The bread always tastes fresh (not dried out or chewy), and the sandwich toppings are cool and refreshing. The employees at this store are friendly and make the experience comfortable. Nothing to complain about here, I bring my friends along and would recommend it to anyone..

text:
The Quiznos of Reno are spread out so far, so it is pretty much the opposite of Subways, which are found on pretty much every street corner. Perhaps it is the low frequency at which I eat Quiznos that makes me like it so much. That toasty flavor is tantalizing.

This location in particular is special because even when corporate discontinued the honey bourbon chicken sandwich (probably the best sauce on a sandwich I have ever had), these guys would still make it for me...until they ran out of the honey bourbon sauce. But the extra effort they made to satisfy me was very significant. Now I enjoy the Baja Chicken or the Southwest chicken to satisfy my spicy sweet chicken sandwich cravings. I wish they would bring back that Honey Bourbon Chicken though!

text:
Walked in, a gentleman was being helped by an employee and another with a scowl on her face. We walked to the ordering area and was asked by the scowler "What do you want?" I replied we're going to look at the menu. She rolled her eyes and turned her back on us.

She turns back around, I begin my order and before I could even finish says nastily "We don't have guacamole." My husband and I looked at each other, he mentioned going somewhere else and I said "Lets go. Her attitude sucks." As we walk out the door, I heard the gentleman customer say "That's two people that have walked out of here for the same reason." ‚Äç 

I didn't get her name, she's young, lighting brown hair in a ponytail. She lost you at least three customers in a matter of 5 minutes.

This is by far my favorite place to get a sub! The Honey Bacon Club is absolutely delicious, the perfect combination & such a treat every time. I personally love it on their Rosemary Parm bread. You can taste the freshness! Their large size is perfect for lunch and the other half for the next day! One of my favorite parts is the sub is the meats and extras, not just thick bread like other places. 
Usually not a big line, only a few people, but they make the subs so quick that its never a long wait. A little pricier than other places I have gone to, but you can taste the difference in quality and it is worth every penny!

categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Salad, Fast Food, Soup, Delis
text:
I haven't been to Quiznos in years. I was in the area and I was really hankering for a French dip. The lady in the restaurant greeted me at the door which was nice. She was pleasant. I got my sandwich to go and off I went. 

When I opened the sandwich, the "saut√©ed" onions looked mildly blanched, but I wasn't going to judge that on looks. They did smell pretty raw still, but only taste will be the judge.

The au jus, however, did give itself away on sight. It looked like diluted chicken broth. It smelled of nothing. This wasn't starting off well, but again - taste be thy determiner. 

Hoo boy. I'm starting to think looks don't deceive. The onions were crunchy and tasted raw. I had to take them off of my sandwich because they were way too overpowering. It tasted like they were put into boiling liquid for 2 minutes max. 

The true crime, however, was the "au jus". Imagine for a moment, dear reader, that you took beef broth and watered it down. Then you watered that down. Then you dumped that into a lake, and took a ladle and scooped up the lake water au jus. That was what it tasted like - nothing, with a sprinkling of something unpleasant. It had no salt, no spice - it tasted like if you took the idea of beef, wrapped that on a carrot, dipped it into celery water, and then hated it. 

I'm sad, because I used to love Quiznos. I hope this is an isolated incident, but I won't be finding out for myself. I won't be back.

attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'None', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Worst quiznos I've ever been too. They have the 5$ daily specials and I work nearby so this is a decent deal. The issue is they refuse to add sauce to any sandwich when it's part of the 5$ special. Example, I want Alfredo sauce instead of mayo, lettuce, pickles, tomatos and olives and whatever sauce it typically comes with. They refuse, no exceptions. They rather make no sale than give me a little sauce. I've walked out twice due to this.

Whoever runs this place is a complete fool. I always remove 100% of veggies which has to at least equal the cost of the sauce. I've debated this on 3 visits and I refuse to step foot into this store again. 

Last visit they sold me alfredo sauce on the side for 40 cents,  but refused to put it on the sandwich.  I asked for all the veggies on the side and threw them away untouched. The can give me all the veggies in the world, but can't give me 3 cents worth of sauce? I've never experienced such horrible service by people who apparently have no common sense.

I would eat here 3+ days a week and now I rarely go. Most of the employees are great, it's only 2 of them who give me issues. I will go there if certain people are working, it just really sucks they are so stubborn over something that shouldn't even be an issue.

attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'None', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
How hard is it to make sandwiches? 

I walked up to the counter around 1 on a not particularly busy day. I ordered. The gentleman behind the counter asks me all the details and goes to (I thought) get started on my sandwich. A couple minutes later, a female employee walks up, and re-takes my entire order again. I ordered the chicken pesto. When it came out the other side of the oven, it had no chicken on it. The other employee apologizes, but instead of re-making the sandwich, just brings the chicken from the little water warmer they put it in, and puts it directly on the sandwich without sending it through the oven. I try the chicken, and it's lukewarm. I ask them to please re-make the sandwich, but instead they just send it through the oven again, coming out burnt on the other side. They still try to serve it to me burnt. I asked for my money back and left.

I understand they aren't getting geniuses to work a Quiznos, but this is ridiculous.

text:
Well, I love Quiznos....but the staff must not replace mask wearing with face shields. No exceptions!! Both ladies there today obviously did not want to be there. Not personable didn't even bother to say how may I help you, just gave me a look as to say tell me what you want. I ordered two sandwiches and two salads and both of my salads have bad lettuce. name: Quiznos
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True'}
text:
I just had the worst experience with this Quiznos.  We decided to order lunch for delivery, since we are having a sort of lazy Saturday.  We spoke with someone, I ordered the Veggie Guacamole and the boyfriend got an Italian.  We also got one bag of chips and two sides of dressing. We were told it would half an hour.

Like that ever happened.  An hour later we are starting to ponder the fate of our sandwiches.  There was no delivery driver in sight.  Then, behold, he pulls up to our house.  Half an hour after they said they would.

We realize there are no chips or dressing in our delivery bag.  We alert the delivery driver who offers to run back to the store to get them for us.  We decline, since it seems silly to send him all the way back to the store for a bag of chips.

My veggie guacamole sandwich is sans guac.  How does this happen? It's in the freaking name of the damn sandwich!  We call management.

We speak to Evan, tell him what was missing from our order, and he immediately responds by offering us to run the sandwiches back out with a coupon for twenty percent off our (which is not likely at this point). While I appreciate the offer, I am not going to wait another hour for a five inch sandwich.

He acts very surprised by the fact that it took an hour, gives me an excuse about how he has been gone all day, just got in, and is making himself food.  

I told him I would rather be refunded for order, at which point he gets confrontational, stating that even though WAY more than half our order is messed up, we can still eat the other sandwich, so he takes off the veggie and the chips (gracious of him, considering I never got the chips) and we hang up.  

The boyfriend bites into his Italian to find veggies that he ordered missing, and at this point I don't even want to deal with them again.

So Quiznos, I was sort of excited to try you again.  I hadn't eaten there in years, and now I am sitting here wondering why I decided to give you another chance.

text: I went in there for lunch and had never been to a Quiznos before, so I took a minute to look over the menu. I thought I'd just keep it simple, so I ordered a sandwich, asking only for turkey and swiss, no rand like it says on the menu, and the first thing she does is glob on a ton of ranch. So I ask her to redo it, and she very rudely tosses the one she messed up out, and grabbed the wrong bread and remade it. I didn't even bother to ask for the right kind of bread. The sandwich tasted fine, except it wasn't even toasty after going through their toaster oven. It was very expensive for what I got, the service was rude, and one of the employees was sitting on the COUNTER when I left. name: Quiznos
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text:
I stumbled across Quizno's a few years ago when they started offering their "Sammies", small flatbread bread sandwiches with a variety of toppings for $1.99 each. 

I never really believed the whole, "Toasted tastes better" motto they used to use, but the Sammies were great, cheap, quick and full of great flavours (bacon, ranch, cheese, hot sauce, etc). You could order a couple and be sated for less than $5. 

Then over time, as Quizno's realized how popular they were and how much time it took to make them, they started raising the prices on Sammies, and eliminated a couple of choices [bye, bye Spicy Chicken Sammie :( ]. Because of that, I stopped going, mostly because nothing else on the menu seemed worth all that great. 

However, bored with the usual places, we dropped into this Quizno's a month or two ago and were pleasantly surprised by our visit. The Sammies were still around, but cost $3.49 each! However, they were quite a bit bigger than in the past, so it was a fair deal once again. I ordered a couple and figured I'd try the Classic Club sub on Rosemary Parmesan bread. 

All I can say is wow! The sub had a great combination of flavours was incredible and I'm a convert into the whole toasting thing now - I just love how the oven crisps bacon! 

But the best thing was that this location offers a variety of free veggies on their subs and Sammies now. Best of all, they really load it up - other Quizno's locations around town are far cheaper with the extra veggies than this location is. Eating a sub at this location is like getting a sub and salad for the same price. 

Now some people might say, who gives a damn about veggies? 

Well I do. 

If I just wanted to scarf down 50 g of fat, I'd go to McDonald's or Burger King instead. I'm no longer a young kid and I like to watch what I eat - and if this location is going to give me a handful of lettuce, tomatoes, green peppers, cucumber slices and mushrooms on my sub for free (they also offer jalapenos, pepperoncini peppers, olives and a couple other choices), then I'm choosing that place over most burger joints when I'm looking for a snack or late night meal. 

Others might say, well so does Subway. Sure they do, but most locations are pretty skimpy on veggies. The prices at Quizno's are also slightly better and I think the food is higher quality - the meat isn't processed meat, but real sliced turkey and smoked bacon and so on. 

Honestly, if you're looking for a great snack that is still somewhat healthy, drop by this Quizno's location and I'm sure you'll enjoy it.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text:
As far as fast-food subs go, Quizno's at one time topped my ilst with its loaded, toasted subs; although the menu is packed with choices I'd typically go for the honey bourbon chicken sandwich and leave full and satisfied. 
Over the years and at various locations, I've noticed the subs seem to have shrunk in size and the ingredients  become a little less commendable in quality and quantity than they once were. 
But my last visit to Quizno's was somewhat enlightening; it appears that, without all those little hot peppers blinding me, I'm not so crazy about Quizno's after all. 
It was my first stop into this particular location and I was sad to see that they didn't have a condiment bar - the store I frequented in Toronto provided a little station with pump jars of barbecue sauce, honey mustard dressing, and, of course, the yummy little hot peppers they offer with sandwiches. I ordered a tuna sub, received the tuna sub, and lingered a little at the till but soon realised that no little plastic cup of hot peppers would be forthcoming. 
I sat down and ate my sandwich. And thought. Head to head, a tuna sub from Quizno's pales in comparison to a tuna sub from Subway. And now that Subway will toast your sub for you, why was I sitting in Quizno's eating a sub-par sandwich? The answer was clear: the hot peppers. And that's all. 
Will I be going back to Quizno's? Probably. Or maybe I'll just do the smart thing and buy a jar of hot peppers.

text:
Being the standard sub-sandwhich place, the food is as good as one can expect. My complaint is the staff. They always look so miserable. They do greet you when you walk in, but when they are busy, they are already dealing with the next customer before they are finished with you. I feel very rushed and almost like an inconvenience. 

And secondly, when you ask for an ingredient on the side, dont roll it up in the fold of the sandwhich paper or put it in a seperate brown bag. This is lazy and extremely messy. Get off your wallet and buy mini 2oz plastic to go containers for pete's sake! Now not only do I have to contend with a messy sub, but I also have to be careful on how I unwrap it. Atleast throw extra napkins in the bag if you are going to try and cut costs/corners for your customer's sake.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
I can't say enough about my experiences in this restuarant after trying to find a place to get food when my regular turkey pesto panini was sold out at a nearby Starbucks. Their cibata sandwiches are extremely tasty, full of fresh ingredients and a super price at 3.99 I think. I almost always have the turkey pesto cibata but recently figured out that you can order the same sandwich and leave out the turkey and replace it with avocado or maybe they call it gaucamole and it's the same price. So you can have a healthy, very tasty veggie version. They also have a preset veggie version of the cibata sandwich, but it's quite different than what I describe above. 

I've always found the staff to be very friendly and they have a super extra bonus - a secured Wifi connection for conducting business transactions if you need to. Much better than the publically open Wifi service next door at the Starbucks. Nothing against Starbucks, I just recently became a gold card member, but this Quiznos has much more to offer in terms of food and Wifi connectivity.

Steve Newcomb
Tucson, AZ

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
Sneaky!  --that's the word that I use to describe Quiznos subs!  Ok, so these little buggers taste great, but do you know what kind of unhealthiness is hiding inside of the torpedoes, bullets, and sammies?  

Fun facts:  
-A regular-sized Oven Roasted Turkey sub has 44 grams of fat
-A regular Tuna Melt sub has 94 grams of fat.  94!
-A chicken Caesar chopped salad has 56 grams of fat

The soups are generally pretty lean and the kids size sandwiches are leaner because they skip the dressings.  The safest sandwiches are the Honey Bourbon and naked turkey and roast beef.  

Bottom line:  hold the cheeses and dressings/sauces here.  Quiznos "sneakily" adds these for free.  Feel free to splurge on the pepper bar!! :)

attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'upscale': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'hipster': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
It was close to 7:30 on a weeknight and since they close at 8, one staff was mopping the floor and the other was cleaning up.  I like the toasted subs so I've never been disappointed with one from Quiznos.  

The staff finished up and washed their hands and asked what we would like.  I decided on the 9 inch mesquite sub with chicken, lettuce, tomato, onion, cheese, bacon and ranch dressing.  With groupon in hand, I had to pay 60 cents for the tax and we took our meal to go.

I was disappointed with the sub.  The bun wasn't nice and toasty and a little bit soft likely from too much ranch dressing they put in.  I should have asked light on the dressing as I don't like too much sauce on my subs.  I won't get this sub next time.

Still a decent location and service so it wouldn't prevent me from going another time.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'upscale': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'hipster': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
The service at this location is what gives it five stars in my book. Always friendly, sincere and willing to help if you have questions about the menu, it feels like they actually give a crap about their customers. 

As for the food, Quiznos in General is my favourite chain sandwich shop. The beef dip is to die for. Honestly, hot and toasty is better. I do like that they're trying to add fresh veg to the menu, but they should give you the option of having it added before or after it goes through the grill, not just after. Whenever I'm in this area, this is always my stop for lunch.

attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'upscale': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'hipster': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Toasted really does taste better. I originally fell in love with Quizno's with their $5 deal for any foot long sub. Unfortunately after a few years this deal vanish, came back for a while, and now is gone again. What happened?

I have also noticed they've been constantly adding new menu items...and not for the better as their new subs are far from cheap. Regardless, I prefer Quizno's subs over other sandwich places due to the amount of meat and toppings they pack into their subs- they certainly don't skimp on anything. One of my favorite selections was their 'Turkey Ranch & Swiss'- the ranch and turkey combination was a delight for my taste-buds!

I this location as it means there are more Quizno's places to choose from on the west side. This location is rarely busy so you can usually find somewhere to sit. Their subs are generously packed that you can make it a full meal, if you choose. If only their prices would be brought down...

text: Went in today because i was driving by and they were advertising an awesome looking crab sandwich.  Upon driving up, I saw 2 employees outside talking, then they came in and washed hands:)  good to see.  I ordered that crab sandwich that were advertising everywhere.  The girl told me they were out of hot crab.  They only had cold crab.  It was a little annoying that they had 3 people there, not one customer and they were out of hot crab?!  I just ordered a soup to go.  While I was paying, I heard the manager telling one employee that "I'll teach you how to do the hot crab next".  It was 2:00 when I went in there, past a lunch rush.  That is something they should have had taken care of already, especially with the advertising.  Not a place I've been to in years, and no reason to go back. The soup was alright.  I'm glad a ordered a regular because if I ordered a small......  I really would have gotten a small... Really small.

text: this place is like tucked away from the main drag of Virginia St., it is near the Target Center, but anyway I went here and found a friendly staff and the sub sandwich was really not that bad! it actually looked like a sandwich, which is more than I can say about the Quiznos in the Walmart Center south of town!!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text:
Just fine.

I always get a turkey ranch and swiss.  None of the flavors dance off my tongue, but it's mmmtoasty, right, so yay?

I'd rather spend a little more for Deli town or a little less for port of subs.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text: Love their sandwiches but the soup leaves something to be desired.  Every time I've gone to this location there has only been one or two people working which can be a little overwhelming to the employees at lunch and dinner rush times.  They are still very attentive but if you're venturing out at these times, expect a bit of a wait.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text: 1st time I went in to this location and they were nice and didn't take long to make my food. But it's a little unsettling to me that their "FRESHLY MADE" guacamole is in a bottle like freakin mayonnaise and it's smooth as butter. I don't know about anyone else, but I actually like a few chunky pieces of avocado in my guac, as that's a telltale sign that it's freshly made. Whatever this stuff is, it almost made me gag and is not quality guac. I hope this changes and Quiznos invests in quality ingredients for their customers like they boast about.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text: This is my first time at a Quiznos ever and I will be going back for sure! Especially with the customer service I received this afternoon! I went in there not expecting for such nice workers! Usually sandwich shops they just want to get you in and out but the two working this Sunday were really concerned about what we wanted and how it turned out, actually making conversation and that is the best feeling when you feel like the workers actually care about what they are doing for you! So I give a big thumbs up to them and the customer service they provide there!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text:
There are a lot of places to get a good s7b but there is no place that makes a TOASTED sub like Quizno's.
Some of their competitors offer toasting but I'd call it "staleling".
Quizno's offers a $5.00 special sandwich every day of the week.
The staff is friendly, their app is okay but the rewards expire fast. But the manager gave me mine even though it had.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text:
I read the reviews and I was so confused about how you can even compare Quiznos to Subway or Port of Subs.  It is like comparing a Louis Vuitton to a cheap WalMart bag.  Anyway, I went to this location and it was fabulous.  The men working were unbelievably kind and lovely.  My sandwich was delicious.  The men helped me picked out two sandwiches for other people.  They, by the way, loved them.  

Thank you for making my experience so awesome!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text: Love quiznos sandwiches... Terrible store. Charged me for the wrong sandwich, I politely corrected it and still had me pay for the wrong sandwich but I wanted to just leave so oh well. And if you were gloves for food prep, do not touch the computer to ring me up and then touch my food again. Or don't take your gloves off after that, touch the screen then grab lettuce and put it on my sandwich with an ungloved hand, without washing your hands between that. And please do not chomp your gum, drop your gum out of your mouth onto the sandwich prep board, then put gum back in your mouth and move my sandwich down the line where the gum just was. And when you drop a grill on the floor then pick it up and make a sandwich on it, when the floors already look dirty..... NOPE.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text:
I normally love Quiznos. It is good quick food. The sandwiches generally taste really good and the mac and cheese is great when it is super cold out. And the soups just make you want to curl up with a blanket and a movie. So yummy. Unfortunately, this is definitely not repeated every trip. 

The last 3 trips to this Quiznos have resulted in ridiculously long waits (2 sandwiches take 45 minutes?), a burnt sandwich that had to be remade, the wrong toppings put on the sandwich as I am telling them I want no additional toppings or only one topping and the one that ends up on it is not even close, and being rung up the wrong amounts. I understand they are hiring and trying to train new employees but I have been going here enough to know that some of the employees have been there for a bit. They are disorganized and it shows. When the sandwich is not burnt (also, if they burn it and ask you if you want it remade and reply "yes" they get annoyed. I am sorry, I like toasty but black burnt is bad) and they make it as requested and charge you for your sandwich (not someone else's) the food is good. As of late though that seems to be a stretch.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text: I just got a great sandwich from the shop on Friday. It was the Basil Pesto Turkey on Rosemary bread. What a great sandwich. Great service and wonderful food! The new owners are really making a huge difference and you can really see that the employees are happy to be there helping the customers. I also really like the calendars. Love the album covers and the great coupons! I'll be going back again and again!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text: First time coming to this location and the service was great. My sandwich was made perfectly and I appreciated the effort in making it just right. I ordered the Honey Mustard Chicken and loved it. The only thing that was a minor fallback was the prices, they are not as cheap as Subway (but they are probably worth the money). I will be coming back to this place because the food and service were awesome!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text:
Kind of Pricey for fast food but if you get a coupon in the mail, worth every penny.

The rosemary bread is great and the sandwiches are better than subway's but as I said earlier, their prices are a bit high. However, with a coupon, it is cheaper than subway.

I recommend the Turkey, bacon, avocado sandwich on rosemary. yum.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text: I work at a local business so I know how important feedback is. When I came in here I really wasn't paying attention to customer service but they were so nice that I actually downloaded this app just to leave a review. A guy and a girl, both extremely kind and talked to us. They told us to let them know how the sand which was (it was awesome). Just a super good experience. I wish it was closer to my house because I'd make it a regular stop.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text:
This is a bad restaurant. I normally am a fan of Quiznos, but this location managed to ruin it. Additionally, I've been a Yelper for years, and this is the first time I've felt compelled to post a negative review. I even took a night to sleep on it and reconsider. I've conferred with friends to ensure I'm not overreacting. I simply cannot get past how much I loathed this experience. Okay, here goes...

First, the food. I have no idea how to describe it other than that at a minimum the veggies were spoiled. They didn't taste right, and when I saw my sandwich being made the guacamole was brown. It also didn't taste like guacamole. I was hoping it was just the effect of how they stored it, but it was definitely bad. I genuinely don't know how I didn't get sick. My coworker was pleased she didn't get veggies. I guess I should be thankful about how conservative they were with providing said vegetables. They young lady making my sandwich clearly was putting as little on my sandwich as she could get away with, but I don't blame her. I'll get to that later.

Second, Environment. I came here at about 11:30. Peak lunch time. The store was completely empty. I should have picked up on this warning sign. The store wasn't dirty, but there were boxes everywhere. Fine, no problem, looked like someone was restocking chips. That's fine, but when I walked up to the counter to order I could see little to no effort was made to keep the working surfaces clean. Again, I'm shocked I didn't get sick from this place.

Third, the service. My coworker and I were both very uncomfortable, and solely because of the manager. I unfortunately did not catch his name, but he came bursting in mid-order and immediately started talking about how hard his day was having to manage two stores. This is a conversation that would be perfectly fine if he and I knew each other. At all. Don't start complaining to random customers about the difficulty of your job. He literally never stopped talking at that point until I left the store. It was wildly uncomfortable. My favorite was when the young lady asked me if I would like any other veggies on my sandwich, and he yelled at her very condescendingly to put the guacamole on there. Her facial expression of pure disdain suggested to me that this guy is truly the dumpster fire that he seemed. The thing that sent it over the top for me at the end was that he asked me how much I wanted to tip him. Tip you for what? Making me and my coworker uncomfortable? For being obnoxious? For clearly demonstrating that you treat your employees like garbage? No. His answer? "Oh, that's fine." No, it isn't fine. You've done nothing to deserve a tip, nor have you done anything to earn my business. Despite that young lady being obviously miserable she managed to offer an acceptable, if lackluster, level or service. It's more than I think I could muster with that kind of work environment.

In short, if you need a Quiznos fix, go to the store on the North side of town by Winco. This guy said he managed two stores, but I've never seen him at the North side store and I've been there many times. Additionally, the friends I spoke with on my experience knew who I was talking about as they've also had poor experiences with this guy. Spare yourselves a disgusting dining experience and go just about anywhere else. You'll be better off for it.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text:
The atmosphere is nothing to write home about as it's a functional simple fast food chain, but dude, that Italian classic sub was absolutely delicious once I go it home and gobbled it up. I love salami and Italian meat products. YUM! Filling and tasty.

The service was especially good. It's in a mini-mall so lots of parking.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text:
Please don't talk on the phone the entire time it takes to make my tuna melt and check me out.  A giggling, lighthearted, smiling conversation; nothing indicated a pressing issue.  It's down right confusing!

I grab a business card at the register thinking I'll drop the owner a note as feedback is always a gift.

Then the clerk randomly tells me about her conversation WITH THE OWNER.  Who she just talked to.  Who 110% knew she was helping a customer.  

This location has really gone downhill in the last couple years... I really hope they can get back on track.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'"}
text:
Service is always great here! The team always greets me with a smile even when it is super busy. I come here often since it is close to my work so a couple of the workers that have been there for a while remember what I like and just confirm if that is what I want again. right down to the free cup of water (since they recall that I do not order soda).

Be sure to get the frequent customer cards, after 10 stamps you get $5 off your next order.

I will continue to come here in the future and bring coworkers when I can.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text:
The reviews are pretty bad but I don't know what people are expecting with airport food. We needed a bite to eat as we had a somewhat late flight. 

We shared the baja chicken sandwich without bacon. The lady who took our order was pleasant as was the manager (I think) who thought we hadn't been helped yet. We didn't wait long as we were the only ones ordering. I'm not a huge fan of Quiznos but when you're hungry and in an airport, you just gotta grab something.

I'm a foodie just like the next one and I recognize that this is not a foodie paradise. It's airport food and I recognize airport food for what it is--convenient.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text:
Not sure why this place has such low ratings.  This place was at par with my expectation of airport food.
FOOD: I got the angus steak sub. They gave me enough meat, it was a bit messy and bread was mostly soggy, but hey, it was filling and less bland (mushrooms are flavorful) than other airport foods I have tried. Ask for a cup of water it's free.
PRICE: ~$8 not bad for a filling airport food
SERVICE: They have enough employees working here, so not a crazy wait.
BOTTOM LINE: If you are expecting airport food, grab a sub, get some sauce, jalapenos, banana peppers and dive in.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text:
I cannot comment on the food as the employees were so rude that I just walked away. 
Reading other comments this seems to be the case often and if management does not read and respond accordingly then they are losing a lot of money. 
My quick story is I got a breakfast sandwhich brought it to the unmanned cash register that had two sides. I chose a side. As this lazy lady slowly walked back she told me I was on the wrong side and then proceeded to check out someone else. I told her to have fun putting my food back and sorry she hates her job so much.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text:
Note that this Quiznos is one of several vendors at the same location at Terminal A in the Tampa Airport, run by the same company HMSHOST. Shown below is partial text from an email that I sent to Tim Juul on February 9, 2014. According to the receipt I got, he is the manager of these combined operations. Sorry for all the detail, but this guy needs to know how bad things are.

Dear Mr. Juul:
 
I have to complain to you about your foodservice operations at Tampa International Airport's Terminal A. I fly to Tampa from Denver just about every month, and have come to dread my breakfast options on these morning return flights, because your company is my main set of options there.
 
Today's case is a perfect example of why I dread it.  Today, as you can see from the attached receipt, I ordered a bacon-egg-cheese biscuit, a fruit cup, and a 14-ounce container of chocolate milk. Nearly every aspect of the transaction could have been improved from your company's side.
 
First off, the prices charged for the product delivered can only be considered gouging. It is ridiculous to charge figures some 50% or more than those charged at high-margin convenience stores in the area. Stating that the rent is more or there are security considerations are not valid excuses. Other airports charge reasonable figures at their food service operations.
 
Also, the layout of the operation at Terminal A requires me to walk through the line at Quiznos, where they were taking orders for breakfast sandwiches. I initially ordered one of these, waited nearly five minutes for it, and then as I continued along the queue, realized that Pizza Hut was selling substantially the same product for much less. What I ended up buying cost some 30 - 40% less than the sandwich I initially ordered from Quiznos. Since there is only one queue, though, the customer is given the impression that the breakfast options at Quiznos are the only ones available. If the customer could easily go to the Pizza Hut counter easily, that would be a great improvement.
 
Next, I had to return the fruit cup I initially ordered as it clearly had been poorly prepared and was not suitable for consumption. If you think your customer should spend over $4 for perhaps 8 ounces of "fresh" fruit, this customer thinks it should be properly prepared and fresh. To me, this means the stems from the grapes are completely removed, and that all the fruit is neither over-ripened, nor not ripe enough to eat. The first cup I got had stems on the grapes, and the strawberry looked mushy. The replacement cup had under-ripened honeydew, and one piece I had to spit out as it was not suitable for consumption.
 
While I was getting the fruit cup replaced, your cleaning staff removed the chocolate milk from my table, apparently thinking that I was finished. Oh well.
 
The service of the operation also leaves much to be desired. On the mornings of these flights, I typically do not have coffee, so that I can sleep during my flight. Even though the time I get up is around 4:30 in the morning for my time zone, I appear to be far energetic and friendly than the staff serving me. One key exception was the gentleman taking my order at Quiznos. He was friendly enough. However, the man delivering the sandwich and the cashier could learn to smile and say things like thank you. Instead, they appear to simply go through the motions.
 
In conclusion, charging reasonable rates, serving better-prepared food, and some training for your staff in customer service relations would go a long way. Because these types of thing happen every time I try to use your company's services at Terminal A, I typically never order anything from you. This morning, I tried again, and you failed again. Your sales to this customer would quadruple or more if you made these small changes.

text:
This place was a mess.  The service was extremely slow and we were the only people ordering anything.  I don't expect it to be lightning fast, but I also don't want to feel like I'm waiting forever.

The food was also pretty bland.  I was thoroughly unimpressed.  Cost was not bad for it, but I had hoped for more.

text: The food at this particular Quiznos is like the food at any Quiznos: okay, not wonderful, but they make a decent sandwich. During the semester there can be quite a line during lunch time, but otherwise it isn't usually crowded. text: This Quizno's is really nothing especially bad or good... In fact, to review it would essentially be reviewing your average, seemingly up to health code, never too busy Quizno's restaurant. I will say however, that it's relatively disappointing. I had a combo deal of a "small salad" and soup for $5. My salad was comprised of the equivalent of two leaves of romaine chopped up with a little chicken thrown on top with a teaspoon of chopped tomatoes. Definitely not worth it. I would recommend going somewhere else for a salad, or making the calorie splurge on A&W Famous Food which is in the same food court.

text: Don't particularly enjoy this food court, because it is stuffy with kitchen heat, and not special. But I keep coming back because of its central location. It is quicker and cheaper than the other nearby upenn facilities. I liked quiznos brand at one point and this one could bring me back into the fold. Everyone notices how extremely nice and conscientious the employees are. And they make a darn good sandwich. I don't want for much else. I would give 4 stars if only the cookies and chips/ combos didn't cost well over a buck but at these prices I had to take a pass on dessert. They are asking too much for ordinary items which are elsewhere for considerably less. I understand this is more a fault of the chain than this particular proprietor.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
Trust their slogan when they say "toasted tastes better". Quizno's invented this form of serving you their subs, and everyone has been copying them since. I originally fell in love with Quizno's with their $5 deal for any foot long sub. Unfortunately after a few years this deal vanish, came back for a while, and I believe is now available, but only on a limited selection and after 5pm.

Regardless, I prefer Quizno's subs over other sandwich places due to the amount of meat they pack into their subs- they certainly don't skimp on anything. One of my favorite selections was their 'Turkey Ranch & Swiss'- the ranch and turkey combination was a delight for my taste-buds! If I was looking for something more satisfying, their 'Black Angus Steak on Rosemary Parmesan Bread' would be my choice- the honey bourbon mustard combined with their zesty grille sauce on the slices of angus steak was....well, zesty!

I would not recommend any of their 'Torpedoes/Bullets'. It's essentially a breadstick with some sub toppings. Their pizza is also surprisingly delicious and is served in a rectangular form.

Is it any wonder that other sandwich outlets like Subway and Mr. Sub are now offering to toast their sandwiches?

attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'None', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: This is my final day ever eating at Quiznos. I use to love this place but they've gone down hill, especially this location on Conference Dr. This was a terrible experience all the way around. The old lady that doesn't speak English is extremely rude, and has no interest in helping anyone. The dining room and menu board lights were out to the point they almost looked closed at noon. Dr Pepper was out, I told the lady and she just said "yeah, it's out". No attempt to change it out. Then I waited to ask about the 3 pepper sauce they usually how've on the pepper bar. I was literally ignored for 5 full minutes! When I did get her attention, she acted like I'd lost my mind. Told me she's doesn't know what that is, then walked away. Another employee came a minute later and got me some. There's rarely anyone here, now I know why. Absolutely pitiful!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "'quiet'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text: I rejected you long ago... but now I want you back! Quizno's is amazing! I cannot believe what I have been missing out on all these years. I tried it once, when it first came to Edmonton, but I didn't like it. I decided to try it again a few months ago, and I've never turned back. I absolutely love their classic veggie sub. There's two types of cheeses, onions, mushrooms, tomato, lettuce, olives, red wine sauce, and guacamole all on a toasted (and delicious) bun... yum! I'm not going to lie or even try to deny that Quizno's is expensive, but it's worth it. The topping are very fresh, and I feel like it's relatively healthy. It's way better than Subway, and I don't mind paying a little extra. For their classic subs, there's three sizes: the smallest is really only a snack, the medium is if you're somewhat hungry, and the largest is if you're really hungry, but you may still need something extra. Other great items here are soups, salads, chili, and flat-bread pizza. I prefer the Manning Crossing location, because they seem to pack the sub with more toppings. Yay Quizno's!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "'quiet'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text: I was a weekly customer at this Quiznos, but never more. Went in with a 50% off coupon 4 weeks ago. Forgot to show the girl my coupon when I placed my order for my usual so she proceeded to make my sub and put it in the toaster. She then noticed my coupon in my hand and removed my sandwich from the toaster, taking about two thirds of the meat off as I watched! I asked her if they make the sandwiches smaller because of the coupon and she said that they had to because they weren't making money on them. The food cost was too high!  I told her that this was not right as the coupon doesn't say that my sandwich deal was subject to being smaller because it was on sale! Bottom line, I paid almost $9 for a bun with maybe two ounces of meat on it and a pop! False advertising at its best, or worst if you prefer. Called Quiznos canada and they sent me gift card for indeterminate amount of money so might try a different location someday, but this dodgy restaurant won't see me again. Despite having all my information, no one from the restaurant, owner, manager, floor sweeper, even took the time to call me and apologize. I am pretty sure that the girl I was talking to and took the meat off my sandwich was the manager as I used to see her do managerial type duties when I went there every Wednesday. If it happens at another location, I'll be very quick to call consumer and corporate affairs to open a case on false advertising. no stars for these guys!!!!!!!

attributes: {'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True'}
text:
I'm sure by now everyone has noticed that Quizno's is a chain that has slowly disappeared all over the STL area. It's easy to forget that there is still one left in the Edwardsville strip mall off 157. In fact, on a Friday night you will be very likely to get served right away compared to all the busy restaurants in that mall. 

Quizno's used to be the bomb. It kind of still is, but in my most recent visit I just felt it was lacking something. For one, they stopped sending me coupons, which I would always utilize! Their sandwiches aren't that meaningful anymore, its like they don't have much life in them. Like flavor, or something. Plus the "I don't give a crap" staff that was working there at the time. I had to wait probably a few minutes to get helped, which set my mood. (There was only two other people there.) Quizno's is still overpriced compared to Subway, but at least they still had their condiments bar which I always dug. I would always get their horseradish and honey mustard sauce every time. Their drink selection is weak as well; if I recall correctly they would have more specialty drinks like raspberry lemonade and tea. I didn't see any of that in my last visit. 

I think in the future I'm just gonna skip Quizno's altogether and watch them fizzle, while I enjoy their competition.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: If you've never been to the Nashville airport then you don't know that it is long in the tooth! It looks like it's getting a makeover because it sorely does need one! My guy and I were on our way home from a two week driving tour of the Southeast. We started in Nashville and we ended in Nashville and we just loved it! However even though our hotel gave breakfast, we had to leave earlier than the hotel was starting breakfast to make our plane. We headed off to the airport and didn't expect to find the best things for breakfast, But we didn't expect to find what we found either! There is nothing but Starbucks and a couple other fried up restaurants with all disgusting food. Finally we came across Quiznos in terminal C. Thank God we did! They actually had egg and cheese sandwiches, bacon egg and cheese sandwiches, ham egg and cheese sandwiches, and different kinds of breads. Nothing fried! Hooray! I had just the plain egg with tomatoes on wheat bread. My guy had ham egg and cheese on wheat bread. Very very good, healthy, and just what we were looking for! Can't wait for the next trip to Nashville when they hopefully have added more healthy restaurants and better choices!

text: Down in the C concourse, this Quizno's has a limited menu but still many of the usual favorites. All sandwiches are the 8 inch size. Service is pretty quick if there isn't a queue but the two times I was past here, there's a queue. Be patient, is all I can say.

text: Terrible customer service. I could not hear or understand any of the employees. They did not make anything that they were doing clear. I regret choosing this place to eat in the airport terminal. I asked them to speak up kindly because of the ambient background noise and they would not. They would just stare at me silently. And since i didn't hear what they had said i would just sit there staring silently too. So after a couple awkward 30 second silent stare-offs i got a sandwich that i think is what i ordered. Not positive but i ate it cuz I'm starving.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Worst Quizno's I've ever had. Quizno's is generally mediocre at best, but wow...

First off, the order was screwed up.

Second, there are multiple health code violations visible from the customer side of the counter. Board of health should be ashamed of itself for permitting this place to stay in business. Unless a passing grade is so low that they're within compliance which is the state's fault.

Third, the sandwich literally fell apart on first attempt to pick it up. 

Fourth, sandwiches are only available in 8" lengths. They don't slice an 8" in half. If it held together, that would be acceptable, but it doesn't so fuck it.

Fifth, the employee exuded apathy and what seemed to be the manager gave some semblance of a crap, so that earned them 2 stars.

I'll be sure to avoid thus dump on my next shuffle through this airport. Terminal C of the Nashville airport is to good food what cancer is to good cells.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: While on a layover in Nashville waiting at the airport we stopped in at Quiznos for a bite to eat. We were so tired of traveling and definitely ready for a meal. I saw this poor employee working alone with a long line of customers, yet despite her stressful situation with so many orders to fill and only herself to meet the demands she greeted us with the most cheerful smile and a warm welcome. Nyshol filled our order promptly with a friendly smile. The sandwich my husband ordered was perfectly prepared as was my sandwich. We ordered the Classic Italian and the  Chipotle Beef sandwich. Both were toasted, warm and perfectly seasoned and ready for pickup in no time. The thing that we were most impressed about was the cheerfulness of a lone employee working extremely hard, quickly serving up great food.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Seriously Nashville airport....your food choices need HELP.  This is the second time I am leaving a bad review for a chain within the airport.  

830 at night.  Food court is still open (at least till 9 pm). 

Get to the counter.  Order a traditional sub on wheat no onion no vinaigrette.  Cold. 

Starts putting it together.  Puts onions on.  Then scoops them off when I remind him no onions.  What if I was allergic?? Scopping them off....not right dude.  

Then....puts it in the oven. Ugh! I choose not to say anything.  Whatever.  I will let it cool down. 

In the mean time, while this is heating, they are using cleaning wipes and wiping everything down. All the nasty surfaces and bins and what not. Pulling things away from the walls etc.  

Ding. Sandwich is done.  Lady tells him to keep cleaning (which she was also doing) and she would finish it.  She pulls my sandwich off and asks if I wanted anything else on it.  ....  I said.... You just grabbed my sandwich with the same gloves youve been cleaning with.  She just looked at me.  I said, you didnt change them. She says "you want me to make you a new sandwich?".  

Ummmm. No.   You have the place taken apart.  I'm guessing any food still out has been handled by those dirty gloves at this point.   So no. I dont want another sandwich.   I literally threw it away and got something elsewhere. 

Ps....the food industry requires hair to be contained when working with exposed food prep items. Her hair wasn't....

Won't be back and I travel this airport every single week.
