text:
This Quiznos is located at the Nashville Airport, Concourse C, near Gate C-14, close to Burger King. 

Yesterday for dinner, I ended up picking Quiznos since the other food choices in Concourse C just didn't have that many choices that I wanted. Also my husband and I were rather annoyed that we were ignored at Tootsies when we tried to eat there right before. 

I came here around 6:55 pm and there was a long line (probably the longest line in this food court). When I got to the register, I ended up getting:

Honey Mustard Chicken Salad, $8.29 after tax- Dressing automatically comes on the side. I liked that the romaine lettuce in this salad tasted fresh and that there was more than plenty enough chicken. There was also shredded cheese and plenty of bacon (which does kind of defeat the purpose of having a salad. My husband ended up eating most of it, adding it to his whopper than he ordered at Burger King, along with my cheese to enhance his meal) and three slices of tomato. I wished there was more tomato but this salad was pretty filling and perfect for one person. 

The employee at the register was nice and she gave me a large cup of ice water while I waited for my salad to be made. Since I did order a salad, wait time for me was not nearly as long as everyone else who ordered a sandwich. One employee saw that there was a chicken salad order and so she worked on that right away. 

Overall, I am glad that I ended up picking this Quiznos for my dinner. The price was not overly priced like some of the other airport food items around and it was nice to have a salad at a layover that was much longer than anticipated (our layover that was originally supposed to be 2.5 hours ended up being 4 hours).

Im a huge sandwich person and Quiznos never dissapoints.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Should've known we were going to be in for a wild ride when they aren't capable of serving the full Quiznos menu. Staff moved extremely slowly, almost to the point of incompetence. 

Bread selection is dismal and it tastes old and dried out. Sandwiches were poorly crafted leading to them falling apart upon opening them and a giant mess while eating them. 

Sandwiches were so cold that the cheese had not melted, and were also missing ingredients on their flagship menu items. They also did not posses the skill to cut sandwiches in half. The bread on my sandwich was so crusty that it broke in half before I could take my first bite. 

Counters are filthy with trash all over them that I guess they aren't bothered to clean up. 

Cashier was also extremely unfriendly.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Mmm...rude. Cold food. Crappy service. Had to wait for someone to come over and take my order. Very rude. Acted like she hated everything about everything. Ordered steak egg and cheese and coffee. She puts coffee on counter and walks off. Figured it was mine but since other people waiting I asked if it was. She grunted something that sounded like a yes so I took it. Get sandwich. I have had Quiznos before and it's mostly good. This one was cold. Hardly any meat. Cheese was actually cold like they put it on after the fact. I don't expect much from airport food courts but this one needs some work.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Probably one of the worst food stops I've had in an airport in recent memory. One gal working her a$$ off, the other with an attitude. This can make or break a business. I see why they went belly up in Texas. Attitude talking to staff (who no one saw): y'all better get your breaks in before it gets busy". Um mam, flights have been delayed all day due to weather. It's been busy all day. Sandwich was edible, her attitude and customer service skills wasn't even palatable.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Probably the worst Quiznos I have ever been. Bread underdone. Toaster doesn't work. Personnel with language barrier and rude.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I haven't had Quiznos in a couple of years since moving from California, I was so excited to get the mesquite chicken. I walked up behind a family of 3. There was one lady behind the counter yelling ( literally shouting) she would only help one person because the employees for Quiznos did not show up and she's been working two stations all day with no break (she was employed for the pizza parlor that shared the space with Quiznos). The employee sees me standing there and shouts, "Sorry I'm  not serving you, I have to go back to the pizza area!"(there was no customers at that moment). Overall disappointing experience.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Took ten minutes to even be greeted by an employee because all three were busy with their menial task, not worried about the line at the register.  When it was our turn, we were simply greeted with a "yes?".  I asked for broccoli and cheese soup and she just said "no.  I'd have to make that and I'm not going to do that."  To top it all off, the sandwiches were sub par.  I can now see why many Quiznos are no longer in business.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Speed or service is not their thing here. It almost seems they are intentionally trying to make you wait while they dilly dally around. And forget about any kind of cheerfulness. It seems like a miserable place to work where nobody cares or is held accountable.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Visited Quiznos in the Nashville airport. It had been years since I had been to Quiznos since they don't have them in my neck of the woods.

Glad I got there early- one other person in front of me. A line quickly formed which normally wouldn't be a problem but the poor worker behind the counter was ALONE! She had to manage order taking, sandwich building, complaint management and she did the very best job she could given her circumstances. One customer couldn't leave it alone even though she offered to give him a meal certificate to take to another restaurant. Kudos to that patient woman!! And shame on that unruly customer.

Sandwich was as good as I remembered and I'd definitely go back if I'm in that airport.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Terrible service, language barrier slow service. You should probably make some changes due to all of the poor reviews at this location.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Long lines but fairly quick service, despite the employees clearly not wanting to be there. 

I ordered the Ultimate Turkey Club with ranch instead of mayo, and declined a drink or side. The cashier was running a script, so I knew what questions were coming by listening to the people ahead of me, but giving her all the info up front instead of waiting to be asked threw her off. I understand, when you get in a routine you get on a roll; my effort to be helpful had the opposite effect. It got sorted out and I paid and kept moving down the line to the pickup area. 

When my sandwich came up, the woman preparing it asked if I wanted lettuce. I said that however the sandwich came was fine, and she just stared at me without saying anything. After a few seconds I declined and she finished making it and wrapped it up.

Weird service issues aside, the sandwich tasted as expected from Quizno's. It was a bit pricier than their normal shops, but it was a hearty sandwich that kept me full for my journey home. I'd stop again if I found myself in that terminal, but next time make sure to follow their lead on ordering.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I was deeply saddened when almost every location closed across the USA. In fact, I thought they were all closed. Recently, I was given a glimmer of hope. So if you are flying in and out of Nashville, you may still enjoy a toasty and tasty sub from Quiznos. 

They were out of the rosemary Parmesan bread when I went,but I didn't care. I was so happy to devour that sub... nothing else mattered. 

I've flown in and out of BNA quite a bit this year but was on different terminals. I will now arrive for flights early to enjoy Quiznos, and upon returning to BNA I will be arriving late to baggage claim. 

I've missed Quiznos.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text:
Years ago, Quizno's never made a pound of sense to me. They charge $8 dollars to Subway's $5, just because they have a toaster. 

Now Subway has a toaster too, as does Wawa, and everybody else in 2007. So recently, a friend and I had little time, and everything was closed in the area, so he dragged me into Quizno's.

I was kinda impressed. You're still paying what you could be for a sit-down casual dining lunch, but the combo includes a decent cesar salad, a drink, and the sandwich selection is much better. After growing disappointment with Subway, I think I might've traded sides and become a Quizno's guy, when it comes to food done fast.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text:
At first this place was okay, but they keep adding new things to their menu that makes it perfect for lunch.

if you are not into their toasty sandwiches, you can get a bread bowl (soup in bread) like the clam chowder with bacon. Or a sandwich meal like the Steakhouse Beef Dip. I don't think you'll be dissapointed with anything you get here if you order well.

They also have breakfast. If you like Wawa's sizzli or McDonald's McGriddle, QUizno's also has pancake sandwiches.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text: Ever since Quizno's ran the ad campaign featuring a singing rat I have been turned off.  Luckily the advertising geniuses behind the rat are not the same people behind the food.  The new commercials show larger sandwiches than Subway, and they are accurate.  At Quizzno's you will get a larger meal for slightly more money, and personally I think it is worth it.

Yuck.  Sooooo not my thing.  I can kinda-sorta deal with a plain turkey sub on whole wheat.

There is little nutritional goodness to be had here.  I simply hate fast food.

But it is cheap.  (You get what you pay for.)

text:
Stopped in for a quick lunch and boy oh boy, was that a mistake. This place is really bad news. I ordered the chicken fajita, for almost 8 bucks, and decided to eat there. First the meal, imho, was awful. They rolled the fajita up like a burrito and the chicken were in tiny tiny pieces, almost like little petite peas, the rest was filled with M
 exican rice. I wanted to gag.
The staff was slow and the place was dirty. Never again.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
text:
Worst Quizno's Ever! Simple as that... We went on a weekday and there was a small line in front of us, maybe two people. We were able to order soon enough, however it took us nearly 20 minutes to get our sandwiches. When we did, the bread was not toasted and the toppings were cold. My grilled onions were raw and still had the skin on them. 

The staff was grumpy and not very helpful. When I asked for a bag and extra napkins, I was given a huff and 1 napkin to go along with the to go bag. With Pickles Deli now in the area I will NEVER go to this Quizno's again.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
text:
I suspect the only reason why this Quizno's doesn't have any prior reviews is because all the other customers died before they had a chance to write one.  Pray for my wife's health.

I only had one bite of her sandwich and that was enough.  I'm not even sure if that was bread they used.  But it was some funky smushy oily nasty substance.  Horrible.

Not to mention this location has that certain je ne sais quoi with the staff and decor.

If you need a sandwich, do yourself a favor and  walk down to Planet Sub or Culinaria.  Or really, any other place.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
text: The workers don't handle the food right and the inside is disgusting. It's old and dirty. The only reason why I would come back here is if every restaurant in St. Louis shut down and this was the only restaurant  open.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
text:
The owner is fairly friendly.  Set-up is a bit strange - different from most Quizno's.

The oddest thing is that since the sandwiches are made in the back they never ask you what you want on your sandwich.  You order and they give you the sandwich.  If I go back I will make sure to specify what I want on my sandwich because unless you bring it up they will just give you the regular toppings.  Noticeably skimpy on everything as well.

Food is not great as far as Quizno's goes (and generally I really like Quizno's).

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
text: Avoid this place. It's dirty and messy. Kitchen is at the back and there are huge open cardboard boxes in the front. Like a giant open pantry! Sandwiches are not good either. Not like other Quiznos. I am not going there again.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
text:
Stopped in here today for lunch just to change it up.  Hadn't been to a Quizno's in while.  I went with their Black Angus on Rosemary. I didn't want to have them add the honey mustard sauce to the sandwich but they did anyway.  I thought that was kind of odd since there was no one else in the place besides myself and my co-worker.  It also took quite a bit longer than I expected since we were the only two people in there.  

The sandwich was ok still even though I requested it without the sauce.  I'm not sure if I'll go back unless I really feel the need to.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
text:
In all the times that I have visited this Quiznos location, I have never seen a smiling face on the staff.

While the food is generally good, on this visit I thought it was odd that my sub didn't taste toasted at all. I managed to one "crunch" out of the meal in my very last bite.

What really made it a poor experience, though, was when I picked up my sandwich and there was so much mustard on it that it literally was lubricating the bag it was placed in. I ended up getting mustard on my jacket and shirt trying to pull it out of the bag. And to top it off, they had no napkins sitting out on any counter. I had to ask the staff to get some for me.

I don't want to say that I've lost faith in Quiznos ability to serve a good sandwich, but definitely the service at this one is lacking and in need of some major improvements. I guess I'm lucky I brought a coupon with me on this visit.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False'}
text: Worst Quizno's franchise I've ever been to. The guy that always works behind the counter is rude and unhelpful. He wears a half-unbuttoned shirt with his nasty chest hair hanging out. He then goes back and makes sandwiches like this, and they seem to ignore special requests like no mayo. Don't waste your money! I would expect better from a downtown franchise in a prominent location.

text: Order took 2 hours to receive. I asked for dressing on the side for both sandwiches which I did not receive. Sandwiches arrived soggy. Soup was obviously cold. text: Chicken pesto ceasar and roast beef and horseradish are my 2 favorite sandwiches here, and I've tried almost their whole menu! This quiznos has one of the most friendliest staffs I've ever met. They are very patient, professional and helpful. Its also close to where I work, and I haven't been able to venture out for about 2 months because this has easily become my go to spot for lunch. They always have dollar off coupons online so be sure to print one out get a delicious sub for cheap.

categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Chinese, Fast Food, Delis
text: I have eaten at this Quiznos several times as it is only a few blocks from my office.  I have not been impressed, especially compared to the quality I receive from the locations closer to my home.  I ordered the Chicken Basil Pesto Flatbread today and I was very displeased.  The flatbread tasted like it had been frozen for song that it got freezer burn before being reheated.  The chicken also tasted frozen.  I don't think I'll be back to this location (or any other, since they removed my favorite item from the menu and can't make it anymore).

categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Chinese, Fast Food, Delis
text:
Quiznos has better meats than subway and their cookies are also better 

This location is the only one in Nashville and they do a good job with mobile orders 

I haven't been inside their physical location yet but they are making quality subs and the price is excellent for delivery

Their toasted subs are amazing, the toppings are great I recommend the chicken carbonara and the black angus steak

(Bring back the Chicken Milano with the green basil pesto sauce and red sun dried tomato pesto!)

If you are going to pickup or takeout Ask if they can toast your cookies  as that was the best thing in the world when I used to visit in person

text: This location always has odd hours. I've always been a fan of Quiznos, but it seems that every time I'm downtown and stop in here to eat then they are closing up shop. The very few times I've eaten here have been okay, nothing special or out of the ordinary for a Quiznos. The only reason that I'm rating it so low is because, the employees always seem like they don't want to be at work, and when I am in the area and head that way, they are always "Closing," and because the parking lot for this location is terrible and small.

attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: When I'm out and about running errands around lunchtime this is my favorite place to eat for a quick cheap tasty lunch.  I like the sandwiches--the Italian and the double cheesesteak are my favorites.  I also like the chili.  Can't beat the price, the quality is good, and if you get a punch card, after the 8th sandwich the next one is free!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: When you talk fast food that seems good for you, a sub place might come to mind. The one sub shop that comes to my mind that is clean, friendly staff and has a consistently good sub is Quiznos. Not the lowest price sub shop but the value for your dollar sub shop it is. I would recommend the steak subs, the peppercorn sub with the black Angus meat. The meat is soft and good flavor I like the bread and meat toasted that's the way they do most of there subs. Now I know a steak sub with cheese and the fixings on top will tip the calorie scale but it has to be less then a big mac, right...

text: Great sandwiches, good workers. The guys there are quick and helpful.

text: Love this place, the staff is friendly and always great food. The prices may seem a little higher for fast food, but given the amount of food and how good it tastes, it is more than worth the little extra.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Called in to place an order and before I could get past asking to place my order, the employee tells me "we're really busy right now, you'll need to call back in 5 min."  I work in customer service as well and know that this is NO way to handle customers.  I would have preferred to have been placed on hold for a few min, asked to take my number down to call me back or something to make me feel like they weren't just too busy for us.  Needless to say our office did not call the location back to order our 8 sandwiches, but rather to let them know we would not be ordering and let the manager know of the poor service we received.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: Had to update this because I didn't give the service enough (or hardly any) credit in my last review. This place is basically run by two guys, I'm assuming the owner and a manager. Both are very friendly and seem to know everyone who comes in. They even like to guess what you'll order based on previous visits. Really nice guys and they make a mean sub. They also are great with honoring the coupons you get in the mail every other week and even let me keep one to use it again. The new pork sandwich isn't half bad by the way, although I'll stick with one my chicken subs about 95% of the time. Forget what I said in my last review, these guys are great.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text:
Always been a big fan of Quizno's. Definitely preferred it over Subway cuz of the amount of meat you get and the actual toasting of subs, not just nuking them real quick. 

This particular Quizno's is very convenient to my apartment, making life easy for me when I don't feel like cooking.  The food is pretty much the same at all locations. It's all pretty tasty. The service here isn't the best. It's sometimes difficult to understand the employees because of their heavy accents.  You can usually figure it out because they ask all the same basic questions about your order. 

In the end, like I said, the food is pretty much the same as usual. Either you like it or you don't. I really like what they have to  offer. It's also nice getting the coupons in mail.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text:
There's absolutely nothing wrong with this Quizno's, but at the end of the day it's still fast food and not worth more than three stars. With that said, this particular location is always very clean and updated, and I've never had more than two people ahead of me. The staff are friendly and seem to enjoy their job, which is always a plus. 

Subway has been getting a pretty bad rap lately, and honestly I don't know if Quizno's is any better, but I definitely prefer it over Subway. Plus, Subway stores always seem to have that weird funky smell, whereas Quizno's smells like toasted bread and meat. Yum.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: Just like any other Quizno's, this place provides a quick tasty sub, soup or salad.  I've been here a couple times and there has never been a crowd.  This may be because it is located in a store plaza that is a few blocks away from Germantown Ave and doesn't draw a lot of business from around Chestnut Hill.  The staff is polite, but I wouldn't consider them overly friendly.  Like most chains, I wouldn't recommend this place for a unique experience, but its definitely great for a reasonably priced lunch.

attributes: {'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'loud'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text:
Surprisingly the food is decently priced for the restaurant itself being inside the casino. I would definitely come here if you're craving Quizno's, but don't expect it to blow your socks off.  They skimp on the meat BIG time. Both my Pesto Caesar Chicken and the hubby's Roast Beef and Horsey were lacking in the meat department. 
The temperature of food seems to be a common issue here based on other reviews and those reviewers are definitely right... It's just not as hot and toasty the way a Quizno's sub is supposed to be!!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
This is a great place to go if you are tired of just regular subs.  Quiznos seems to take the boring sub and adds some life to them.  It's a great place to grab lunch on the go and some of their subs are about 500 calories, which is how much you want to consume per meal.  If you need any help with ordering let me give you some great suggestions.  The Turkey Ranch and Swiss (~500 calories) is really good, it's good when it cold but it tastes much better when it's warm.  I suggest you eat all of these subs right away after they come out of the oven.  Anyways, back to my recommendation, this sub has some turkey, Swiss cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, red onions and ranch dressing.  It's a really good sub, but there are other subs that are just as delicious.  The Traditional (~500 calories) with roast beef, turkey, ham, cheddar cheese, olives, lettuce, tomatoes, red onions and ranch dresses.  This is a great sub if you can't decide on which kind of meat to get.  Why get one when you can get three!  If you don't really care for ranch dressing then go with the Honey Bacon Club (~500 calories), it comes with turkey, ham, bacon, Swiss, lettuce, tomatoes, red onions, and Honey-French dressing.  It's really tasty.  Another great tasting sub is the Classic Italian sub with ham, salami, pepperoni, capicola, mozzarella, olives, lettuce, tomatoes, red onions and Red Wine Vinaigrette.  This is a dream come true for us Italians!  

The employees are really fast and very friendly.  The store can get pretty busy during lunchtime so get there early to beat the rush.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Really, I don't expect too much from Quizno's, but I still don't expect to find "lettuce butts" in my salad. But the salad I ordered had some smaller lettuce butts in it. I also find it odd how the menu indicates that the salads come with dressing, but in reality, you need to go ahead and put the dressing on the salad and toss it yourself.

And i find that most of the food tastes a little too pre-fabricated and sodium heavy for my tastes. The garlicky flavor of the flatbread seems less fake than the Olive Garden's breadsticks, but not by much.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I went here after a long time of avoiding Quiznos and I was so disappointed.

I went in and ordered a medium honey bourbon chicken sub and a small chicken noodle soup. The soup was pretty good, it was hot and it wasn't mushy. I was so disappointed in my sub though. The bread wasn't very fresh, in fact, it was sort of squished. The toppings weren't fresh either, and the chicken was the only thing that wasn't ruined in this sandwich.

I'll stick to subway from here on out.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: Cheap owners who up-charge you for every change and substitution you make on any sandwich.  (30 cents extra for black olives!). They don't participate in any national promotions.  They charge you extra for different breads.  The menu has shrunk, and not in a good way.  Between the cheapo managers and the teenage worker who plopped my sandwich down so hard that it lost half its ingredients before I even got to it, and the fact that a medium combo with chips and a drink cost me $9 freaking dollars just makes me want to punch them... attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text:
Although my server was friendly, I find the quality in poor taste.  I had ordered my sub and requested a few changes.  I don't mind paying extra but he said he couldn't do this.  I know this wasn't true because I was in a few days earlier and the person charged me.30 cents for each additional change.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text:
Stopped in here for a quick lunch. 

I order a sub listed on the menu and say without cheese or mayo, please. The woman preparing my sandwich proceeds to ask me what I would like on it. I was a little confused at first... I thought she was asking me what toppings I would like. So I repeated that I want the exact sub (I believe it was "the traditional"), nothing additional, and please don't add cheese or mayo. This exchange goes on for about a minute before I realize she wants me to build my own sub. 

So I just read precisely what is listed for the sandwich.

She then begins to throw a tantrum as she's building my sub... I look at my boyfriend and he is equally baffled to why she is rolling her eyes and irritably tossing toppings on my sandwich. One thin slice of ham, one thin slice of turkey and loads the rest with lettuce (should have purchased a salad). Then tops it with cheese. 

I remind her that I do not want cheese on my sandwich and she sighs and chucks the cheese back in the bin. She then asks me what dressing I would like and I said none. She (as expected) rolls her eyes and began to build my partners sandwich. Why she took offense to us I am not sure... Oh and the cashier girl had the same approach with us.

Very bizarre place, even if the sandwich's were tasty (which they weren't) we wouldn't come back, sorry.

The food was always top notch, toasty, and friendly service. Farewell, friends. Hope to see you open a shop or restaurant elsewhere soon.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "u'no'"}
text: Stay away if you don't want to up-chuck! We ordered two sandwiches. Neither my wife nor I could finish our food. My bread smelled foul, as did my wife's. She threw up her entire meal and was sick for two days following this dinner. We went there at 5 o' clock on a Friday evening. This place should've been buzzing with customers hungry for dinner - we were the only two customers in there, and when we went in our sandwiches had been prepared ... and stuck on top of their industrial fridge top. Pretty sure customer orders don't go up there. Never again.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "u'no'"}
text:
Being a chain restaurant you kind of know what to expect going in. 
In this particular location the quality of the food was on par with others I've been to. I'd even venture to say they were a little more generous with the meat and cheese (an important thing to me as I don't get any veggies on my sandwiches). 
What really stood out to me was the staff. They were very friendly and inviting. More times than not a chain feels kind of cold and robotic, this was a different experience. If you're looking for something familiar and great service stop in here.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "u'no'"}
text: Hey--- give this guy some love!  Great sure-fire quick hit for lunch... Great steak&mushrooms on flatbread.  Feed your soul.  FEED IT!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
text: Lousy customer service. I asked the woman to bag my order and sh pointed at a stack of plastic bags and said "there they are". Would not have been a big deal but I was at the airport toting a carry on, a backpack and a Starbucks coffee and they couldn't take a moment to put my bacon egg & cheese flatbread sandwich in a plastic bag. The bacon was undercooked too. AVOID Quizno's At TPA!

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
text:
It was very late, almost closing time.  The woman who attended me was very nice and helpful.  I wanted to go to Shula's Burger next door, but they were ignoring me when I walked up to the counter and I assumed they were closed.  While enjoying my food from Quizno's, I noticed someone waiting on a customer at Shula's Burger.  Funny that Omar S.'s review mentions a lack of service and wanting to go to Shula's Burger next door instead.  I suppose it depends on the day and time you arrive and who is working.  

I had a salad, with all the vegetables, no cheese, and guacamole.  It did the trick.  Would it be my first choice at lunch or dinner time?  No.  Was I grateful?  Yes.

text: Not much seating, the places on either side block off their seating.  Okay employees and pretty fast service.  My toasted sandwich was pretty good, I like the sub toasted, I think I like this better than Subway.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
text: Husband was hungry so he got an Italian sub. Usually airport food is high priced and marginal quality but he said the sandwich was actually very good and fresh. He can be your worst critic do must have been pretty good for him to say so. Service was very fast which is nice for an airport.

attributes: {'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
text: Very over priced. Subs are ok and there isn't much of a selection.  They do offer free refills on fountain drinks but then you need to hop on an airplane with tinnie tiny bathrooms :/

attributes: {'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
text: Love the sandwiches at Quizno's. This particular location has horrible and rude service. In addition there was 6 employees standing there chatting and not working. Took me 15 minutes to get my sandwich. I will not come back to this Quizno's. Recommend Shula's Burger next to it.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': True}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
text: Friendly staff. Fast service. Food just ok. Breakfast subs in the morning and regular meat/veggie subs served all day. I definitely prefer their regular subs over their breakfast ones.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: I have to start this review by stating that I love Quiznos!  Of all the fast food sandwich chains they are and have been my fav for years.  I just recently moved back to Reno (yay!) and this store is the closest one to my office.  Over the past few months I've been here several times but today was the last.  Almost every time I go in there's been at least one employee eating in the food prep area and one time the employee was eating soup and set the bowl (not finished) down right on the prep counter to help another employee.  The prep station on the back wall always has personal items like cell phones, sodas, food from other restaurants (?) sitting on it.  When I commented on it one time the response I got was "Oh, we don't use that to prepare food anymore."  Well...It's right there in the prep area and it's disgusting.  And today when I paid with my credit card I told the woman that rung me up that I wanted the receipt but she threw it in the trash.  I reminded her I wanted it, she apologized and reached into the garbage, pulled it out, gave it to me and grabbed the next sandwich for the guy behind me with out washing her hands.  no, no, no...won't be back.  Two stars only because I love Quizos, just absolutely not this one.

text: My charge card company notified me this morning that a $7+ tip was added to my $15+ dollar order a few days ago. We enjoyed the food and the drive thru convenience, but not the scam

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: Why didnt I read the reviews first! Stopped after my son's baseball game. Hadnt been visited this location because the last time the inside was dirty and weird customer service. After waiting 20 minutes in the drive through, no toasties(yet they are still on the menu), no lettuce... they cant process my debit card because their system was down.  After I saw who was making my sandwich I was leary anyways. After 25 minutes of dealing with this place I left with my baby, 3 year old and my hungry 8 year old. We will not return, how do you tun a business like this?

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: Really disappointed by the service my mom and I received here at this location. I am a huge Quiznos fan and was treated with tons of attitude by a lady working there. I don't know if she was the manager or what but we felt uncomfortable just placing our order. On top of that the food took forever to be made and we weren't even greeted at the drive through window with a hi... just the total. Oh and she forgot our chips! I recommend a different location or different sandwich establishment.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: This place is so disgusting. We are here a few weeks ago and it seemed like they were short handed and either the manager or the owner was working. The salamander that cooks the sandwich wasn't working and they had to remember to pull the sandwich out before it burned. But the worst part of all was that the manager was handling money and making sandwiches without washing his hands. He would even keep the cheap plastic gloves on, handle the money, then NOT change gloves or wash hands (which is required to do BOTH) and the. Make more sandwiches. He did this about 10 times while we were sitting there. I wish I would have recorded him. The entire 30 min we were there the "manager" guy touched money and food without washing and the other guy worked the drive through and made sandwiches without washing his hands. Also the manager guy has on shorts and no apron. I will never go back. I thought for sure I would have gotten sick.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: Terrible Service. I ordered their special sandwich for the month and neither of the two guys working on the sandwich knew how to make it or what went on it. Then it didn't even taste good. The quality is low certainly but the service has never been great.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: Have been going here since 2006.  Last week went and didn't order it smelled like cigarette smoke inside as people were smoking outside and both doors were wide open. Went today a week later as I figured they might have been having a bad day. However this time it was worse. Bathroom door lock still broke, new girl was trying to gigure out how to make a sandwich from the directions.  Sandwich work areas trashed at 11:30am? She couldn't get a container of pesto sauce to pour as the tip was dried out so She stared pounding the bottle tip on the trashed work area. Also, another employee was having a loud discussion with the cashier about how horrible another employees was. Wow, never saw a place take a dive so quick. Didn't order, just left.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: I used to love Quiznos and I used to like this location... until today... First off... the lady that took my order and thank me for the tip, kudos to you. Now the other lady in the backroom, who mocked me in a condescending tone, "woo, hoo... $2 dollar in tips today..." You know what? I normally don't even tip for fast food, so be greatful, don't be a #$!%!. Finally the sandwich or the lack thereof. 8inch sub with barely any meat and over sauced to make up for it... no thanks.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: Closed the lobby at 720 pm to clean although the hours state open until 9.  Took my business elsewhere, and won't be back.  Very unprofessional, lousy customer service.  Had to give 1 star, but they don't deserve it.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: Seriously!? 20min wait in the drive thru, mind you only one vehicle ahead of me and one sandwich ordered. If you want a quick lunch, in and out, don't bother with this place. Chicken Carbanaro was decent, but then again it's a sandwich so can't screw up that much.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text:
FAIL! 

I'm so angry that I can't even get into how bad this place sucks. EVERY.SINGLE.TIME we go in there. You'd think we learn after the first time they screwed up. They somehow managed to get all the food out of order and then looked me dead in the eye and swore all my food was in there- only to get home to find out my soup was NOT in there! I called back, furious to which they told me they'd comp our next meal. Neat. But it still doesn't change the fact that I HAVE NO LUNCH. 

Well the other day I was craving Broc. Ched soup so I sent my boyfriend to get some. I SHOULD have sent him to Deli Towne, but I figured this was closer, and less of a hassle. Ha. He didn't feel like messing with the 'look up our name' crap to get a free lunch so he just paid for it. And wow. Where do I start? 

The "soup" was in fact just orange water. Literally. It was the consistency of WATER. No chunks of vegetables or any cheese flavor- it tasted and looked exactly like someone realized they were almost out of soup and added a ton of water to it. NASTY! FAIL!  

Then, he couldnt even eat his sandwich! Some brainiac at Quiznos decided that it would be a good idea to put the large sandwiches in this tiny paper bags- so here was a sandwich with bits of chicken and other various loose small ingredients shoved into a little bag, impossible to eat. He had to rip the bag all the way open, cut it himself and then scoop his sandwich back together! 

I was furious, I called and the manager gave me some bullcrap excuse about how sometimes the soup is chunky and sometimes it's not, that they cant control how thick it is! WTf. are you kidding me? Of course you can retard- add less water! Then he gave me some crap about Quiznos trying to 'go green' and that's why they use the bags instead of CUTTING and wrapping the sandwiches. Again, WtF?  Maybe i'm missing something, but how does not CUTTING the sandwiches save the earth? And if you're gonna stick the sandwich in a stupid little bag- then why not just wrap the damn thing? 

I told him that they've stolen enough money from us, from not giving us our food to giving us a product that was very obviously inedible. How the hell am I supposed to eat "soup" that isn't thick enough to stay in a damn spoon? Shall I drink it through a straw? No, because it was nasty, orange/cheese colored water! Then I hung up on his dumb ass. I had my keys in my hand ready to go down there, and demand every dime of my money back- from this order and the previous...alas, my boyfriend "the peacemaker" - calmed me down by promising me soup from Deli Towne. He knew how close I was to going down to Quiznos and throwing their "soup" at their window. 

It is AMAZING to me, that I know so many intelligent people that cannot get jobs in this economy- and the idiots running Quiznos have jobs. Shocking. Either way, I will never, ever come back here. Ever. 

I ended up going to Deli Towne for my soup- where I should have gone in the first place. Argh.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: So my boyfriend and I have eaten here twice so far and will continue to do so! Their customer service is above and beyond! Their bathroom door was still broken when I ate their two week ago like other reviews state but that's an easy fix. But not only management but all of the employees are kinda and professional, and what was interesting to me is that they treat it more like a restaurant than it is fast food. The food was amazing, prepared quickly with no issues. When my boyfriend told me they had only 2 stars on yelp it made me sad because they are going above and beyond! Having worked at a subway before I'm usually a hard critic on sandwich places because most of them are slow and half assed about their job, and barely greet you. But this Quiznos everybody greeted you politely and the manager even comes by to tables making sure everybody's satisfied and offers to take trays for you and offers to wrap up unfinished sandwiches. Like cmon that's high quality restaurant behaviour. I got better service here then I do at most restaurants.

text: I was given two coupons to Quiznos for a "free kids meal" and a $5 meal deal at the Reno Air Races this year. I was excited considering I hadn't been to Quiznos since the launch of the Sammie. When I brought the kids in today for our "Free Lunch" we ordered our meals and proceeded to the "pay here" that's when we were told we could only use one coupon.
