attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text:
So, despite all the negative reviews I went into this Quiznos the location the other day for lunch, as I was really craving a Quiznos sandwich.  I was cautious when I entered the store, but found everything to be in order and clean (as far as I can tell) . Looked like a totally normal Quiznos. 

I got up to the order station and inadvertently sighed as I was looking at the menu (lost in my thoughts on what to get I guess). The lady behind the counted decided to mimic me and sighed back, which I thought was a little odd. She was smiling though, and I didn't take it to be too malicious so overall it didn't bother me too much. I had no issues ordering and the employee that was helping me didn't complain at all about my requests (I was essentially building my own). I wouldn't say it was the most professional demeanor I've experienced in a sandwich shop, but again nothing malicious so I didn't think it was a big deal. I could see how it might bother some people though.

The employees on the back half of the sandwich line were very friendly and courteous, so no problems there.  Overall I was say everything seemed to be ok with this location, and I'd probably come back here again when I was in the mood for another Quiznos sandwich.

text: I had a grand opening for my new shop. I used Quiznos to cater the event. I had no idea that they did that. I met with Carol, who went over all the options. The day of our event, she set up a wonderful spread, she included table cloths, flavored water and sandwiches, soup and cookies for my customers. It was more than I had even imagined and my customers were so impressed. The food was wonderful, hot and the variety was excellent. I would highly recommend Carol, Brian & Tipa, the Quiznos catering staff for any event. I will most assuredly use them again in the future!

text: Used to love this place. My office is close. Frequently bought lunch here twice per week. Today was my last visit ever. text: Sup everybody..I can't remember how long Iv been coming to Quiznos..First time ever was when they had a location in the "Good Guys" shopping plaza now it's Costal Vrida on fire creek...then I use to go to the one in sparks by the now flowing Tide..the old Sparkys..Then I went twice to the one in the Target shipping center on S Virginia St..Yes Iv been around lol...But as y'all can see I put twice..there's just something about the Quiznos in the target shopping center..it don't taste right the vibe is off the Staff and Manager just don't seem like they want to work..seems like they are there just for a paycheck....But this one here...the moment u walk threw the door you get greeted by all the staff..with a smile and they work to work not just for a paycheck and by now the manager the short Asian lady knows my and rest of my families order by heart it's crazy but it's always OnPoint so year this is the best one in town Enjoy!!

text: Was greeted with a smile and warm hello as soon as I entered the door. My daughter ordered the meatball sub kids meal with Ruffles cheddar and sour cream chips, and pink lemonade. I got the Greek chicken grilled sub with a small Harvest Chicken salad. The wait was brief as there were no other orders ahead of us. My sandwich was flavorful with it's tzaziki dressing and banana peppers. The salad was ok...I'm not a fan of iceberg lettuce, even if it's mixed with other greens.   Checkout was easy, and we had no issues getting a table. Not a place I frequent often, but seem to enjoy it when I do.

text: Since this location is shut down and I am no longer employed here I can finally write a review.... I worked here for a year and I have to admitt I loved my job and I'm sad to see it go. To all of you negative customers I apologise if you experience here sucked but for a while we had crap employees and at times yeah we might have been slow but at the end of the day it was worth it especially when we had customers that we're understanding. Just a little info about the owner who you guys were hating on in your reviews he would come in at 8am and work till 10 sometimes almost 11pm everyday just to help his employees out and take care of his customers. If you think it's easy think again. I remember a few of the people on here who wrote reviews that we're bad and you know you were wrong and full of it with what you say you experienced. Just curious to who put you up to it?? But I will admit if you were a jerk well you probably got treated like one.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text:
This place use to be amazing! But it has gone downhill faster than a boulder down a steep mountain. The manager has never managed a store before and is constantly distracted. I've gone in multiple times where he's listening to music instead of helping. I've also have sat in their drive thru for 40 minutes just for someone to take my order because no one wants to pick up a headset and take an order. I was waiting behind a large car full of people and the people working there chose not to have them park so they could get other people through. In fact i watched the person behind me get out of there car and walked to KFC and came back with food half way through us sitting there. Then at the end the manager didn't apologize for anything. 

Overall this place has become shit since the last manager left.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1'}
text: This is the worst experience I have ever had. The order was messed up (I had an order of tots with no jalape√±o and my order had them and there was a bag of chips missing). They ignored all special instructions. Now let's get to the real problem, the manager or supervisor, Brian... whatever his position is, is running a scam on orders. I placed my order online for myself and 6 of my coworkers, I received an email order of my receipt confirming my total, as seen below. My coworker gets there to pick it up and one sandwich was discontinued, so my coworker order a new sandwich, no big deal. He then proceeded to tell the person picking up the order that there was an owed balance of about $21. All of the sudden there were 9 orders of tots added to my order, equaling the same amount that was supposedly still owed. Brian refuses to give me a copy of my receipt, he held it close to the register and practically whispered that we still owed &21. But showed my coworker and told her she "can take a picture of it" and he "isn't going to eat all the tots himself" because "this has happened before". My coworker showed him a copy of my online receipt and Brian told her that he has to go off of his system because "someone clicked the button to add 9 tots" after the order was completed and charged. Yeah, right... I called to complain about my incorrect order, missing items, and fraud and they never returned my call. Corporate here I come... make sure you check your receipt here!

text: Less than impressed. As we drive up to place our order the guy goes "well see about getting your sandwiches to you, we're pretty slow here". name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text:
This location has super friendly franchise owners! I usually change it up during Saturday work lunches and this is one of my favorite destinations and it has been for a few years now. They have quite a selection of menu items from toasted subs to soups and salads, and they even have cookies and brownies for treats.

Usually, this place is super busy during the weekdays since it is really close to Boeing, bioMerieux, the US Post Office (I think it's their sorting facility?), a few other warehouses and some other businesses I am not too familiar with. However, it is quite laidback on Saturdays which is why I mostly prefer coming in here for a quick bite to eat. 

This place is always well-kept with condiments well-stocked especially during their peak hours. I have never used their drive-thru but it seems like they do well keeping up with it. We have always dined inside and it's always been a clean location. I love how the owner and his son remember their loyal customers and are always so pleasant to everyone!

As far as the food goes, they pretty much have every menu item available at all locations. I usually go with their tuna or turkey subs, or some soup and salad. A colleague of mine have had their brownie and cookies and said they were all great!

text:
This Quizno's is the best one I have ever eaten at. It's really big inside, has a drive thru and the staff are great. Went there yesterday for the first time and again today for lunch! text: I use to go to the Quiznos in st. Charles on a weekly basis. Since they have closed we decided to make the 20 minute trip to Hazelwood. The sandwiches are always delicious but I was very disappointed on my latest visit... I paid for extra meat on the mesquite chicken sandwich and sadly less than half of my sandwich actually had chicken on it(I really wanted that chicken.) I always order the same sandwich and I have noticed over time it has come with less and less tomatoes and lettuce. That I could have lived with but COME ON Quiznos for $9.20 you have to give us more than bread and ranch. #donttakethechicken

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text: If you want the best sandwich experience you've ever had, definitely visit this store.¬† My husband and I had never been to a Quiznos before so we decided to give it a try. I had a taste for a hot sandwich and to my surprise all of there sandwiches are prepared hot. The owners are a husband and wife team who were extremely nice and knowledgeable about their menu and product combinations. I ordered the Angus Beef Sandwich with chipotle added and my husband tried the French Dip.  Hands down, these were the best sandwiches we ever tasted in our entire lives. The bread was toasted perfectly and the meat was extremely tender and flavorful. Like Quiznos says, "Eat Up. MMM...TOASTY!"

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text:
Oh Quizno's, how I missed you.
This restaurant used to be open in Arnold off of Richardson Rd. It sadly closed down a few years ago. Their breads were oh so delicious and I loved the salads, too. I wasn't so pleased when I saw how many calories though in a steak salad. How can a place like this pack so many calories in a teensy salad? It had to be the bread!
Anyways, this location is so close by to my work, it ain't funny. I would have to walk on over and order what I want. I ordered a small prime rib sandwich on rosemary bread. 
The price was a bit expensive for a small sandwich, over $8 for just a sandwich and a Sobe drink, but the price was so well worth it. The sandwich had a marriage of different kinds of flavors in my mouth.
Trust me if you like prime rib, the steak, you will totally dig this sandwich! 
And the customer service? Amazing for a Hazelwood location, and I have seen a lot of bad customer service at several sandwich shops.
This is definitely will be my location on a once in a while, a break from the horrible cafeteria food from my building.

name: Quiznos
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text: I absolutely LOVE Quiznos. I will drive 30 minutes out of my way to stop by. I don't remember loving it so much when there were multiple locations, but now that there's only one I'm hooked!!! The chipotle turkey is most definitely my favorite. I loved the ciabatta when it was available. My husbands favorite is the peppercorn steak. It's their sauces that make their sandwich so freaking good!!!
